All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddPartController
    The AddPartController is responsible for simulating a user interface that allows a user to add a Part to the Inventory
    AddProductController
    The AddProductController is responsible for simulating a user interface that allows a user to add a Product to the Inventory.
    InHouse
    This is a subclass of Part, which dictates the Part object being In-House
    Inventory
    This is the Inventory that is used to manage the list of all Parts and Products.
    Main
    Main class to start the application
    MainController
    The MainController class is responsible for simulating a user interface for managing the Inventory of Parts and Products
    ModifyPartController
    The AddPartController class is responsible for simulating a user interface that allows a user to modify a selected Part from the Inventory
    ModifyProductController
    The ModifyProductController is responsible for simulating a user interface that allows a user to modify a selected Product from the Inventory.
    Outsourced
    This is a subclass of Part, which dictates the Part object being Outsourced from a different company
    Part
    Supplied class Part.java
    Product
    The Product object is an object that contains associated parts that make up the product.
